<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880307-0032 </DOCNO><HL> Lockheed Wins $251.1 Million Of Navy Orders </HL><SO> </SO><CO> LK TX LIT SUN GQ ROK ML RTN UTX LTV GE </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Units of Lockheed Corp. received Navy contracts totaling $251.1 million for development and production of the Trident II missile and for C-130 aircraft wings.    Texaco Refining andamp; Marketing Co., a unit of Texaco Inc., received a $109.3 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    Litton Industries Inc. received a $74 million Army contract for night-vision equipment.    Sun Refining andamp; Marketing Co., a unit of Sun Co., received a $60.1 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    Grumman Corp. received Navy contracts totaling $55.8 million for production of E-2c and A-6 aircraft.    Calcasieu Refining Co. received a $52 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    Units of Rockwell International Corp. received Air Force contracts totaling $49 million for space infrared-sensor test services and B1-b aircraft improvements.    Units of Martin Marietta Corp. received Army contracts totaling $40.5 million for targeting and night-vision equipment for helicopters, research on &quot;autonomous&quot; land vehicles and equipment for Copperhead projectiles.    Atlas Processing Co. received a $37.9 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    Raytheon Co. received a $32.3 million Army contract for missile-system improvements.    The Chemical Systems division of United Technologies Corp. received a $28.4 million Air Force contract to remanufacture Minuteman ICBM rocket motors.    LTV Corp. received Army contracts totaling $26.7 million for hyper-velocity guided projectiles and rocket-system support.    Units of General Electric Co. received contracts totaling $22.6 million to develop weapon-control technology for electromagnetic guns and produce T700 helicopter-engine equipment for the Army, and to store communications satellites for the Air Force.    Steuart Petroleum Co. received a $19.9 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel.    Western Petroleum Co. received a $12.7 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for jet fuel. </TEXT></DOC>